{
  "_note": "Self-host mapping example (workplan 0010). Copy to a real name ending in .json in this directory (e.g. mapping.json) and edit. Files ending in .example are NOT loaded. Every *.json here is scheduled on startup. Credentials are referenced by ENV VAR NAME (tokenFromEnv / passwordFromEnv), never inline — set those variables in deploy/selfhost/.env.",
  "tenantId": "00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
  "mappingId": "11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111",
  "schedule": { "cron": "*/15 * * * *" },
  "source": {
    "type": "imap-oauth2",
    "host": "outlook.office365.com",
    "port": 993,
    "user": "you@example.com",
    "auth": { "kind": "xoauth2", "tokenFromEnv": "SOURCE_OAUTH_TOKEN" }
  },
  "target": {
    "type": "jmap",
    "baseUrl": "https://mail.example.net/jmap",
    "user": "you@example.net",
    "auth": { "kind": "basic", "passwordFromEnv": "TARGET_JMAP_PASSWORD" }
  },
  "_note_domains": "The appliance runs all four domains (mail/calendar/contacts/files). The mail domain uses the top-level source/target above. To also sync calendar/contacts/files, add a \"domains\" block with caldav/carddav/webdav source+target entries per domain, each { enabled, source, target }. See docs/selfhost-quickstart.md and packages/shared/src/config.ts for the schema."
}
